  'Total Earnings must equal Publisher Commission plus Digital Wallet.',
  'Slide 3 must be KPI Summary using kpiSummaryTable in advertiser-style tabular layout. It must include Conversions, Publisher Commission, Digital Wallet, and Total Earnings, and it must not include Clicks, AOV, or ROI.',
  'Slide 3 conditional format rule: in the % Variance row use green text for positive values, red text for negative values, and amber text for zero/N/A (source: kpiVarianceColorHintsTable).',
  'Slide 4 must be Program Level Analysis using programLevelBreakdown table, ranked by Publisher Commission descending. The first visible column must be Program ID, followed by Program Name, then Publisher Commission, Digital Wallet, Total Earnings, Conversions, Order Value, Publisher Commission YoY %, Earnings YoY %, and Conversions YoY %. Do not show Clicks, Clicks YoY, Sales, Sales YoY, AOV, or generic Commission labels on this slide.',
  'Slide 5 must be KPI Highlights using the agent-generated KPI Highlights section first, then kpiHighlightsTable and kpiHighlightNarrativeTable for numeric backup. Mirror the advertiser QBR style: concise business implication headlines followed by the supporting current, previous, and YoY values.',
  'Slide 5 depth rule: include 8-10 data-backed bullets where space allows; cover core KPI movement, named growth/decline programs, efficiency movement, total earnings including digital wallet, and at least one risk signal from supplied tables.',
  'API scope rule: Slide 2 bottom summary analysis and Slide 5 KPI highlight narrative must be derived from full API scope (allProgramsApiScope + KPI totals), not only the displayed 12-row programLevelBreakdown subset.',
  'Slides 6-7 must be Movers & Shakers tables: commission and conversions only. Do not create a Clicks movers slide.',
